## Review Sidecar Template

The `.review-needed.md` file MUST follow this structure:

```markdown
# {Schema}.{ObjectName} — Review Needed

> Items requiring human domain expert review. Generated alongside the wiki documentation.

## Reviewer Corrections

> **Instructions**: Add corrections below. Each row becomes a Tier 5 (domain-expert confirmed)
> override on the next pipeline rerun. Use `glossary` in the Scope column if the term should
> also be added to `knowledge/glossary.md`.

| Column / Topic | Current (wrong) | Correction | Scope | Reviewer | Date |
|----------------|-----------------|------------|-------|----------|------|

## Tier 4 (UNVERIFIED) Columns

{All Tier 4 items from the Elements table}

## Columns Needing Clarification

{Items where the pipeline found conflicting or ambiguous evidence, regardless of tier}

## Structural Questions

{Questions about the object's design, schema, or ETL that cannot be answered from code alone}
```

On **rerun**: If a previous `.review-needed.md` exists, read `## Reviewer Corrections` first.
Apply all entries as Tier 5 overrides. In the new sidecar, carry resolved corrections forward
with `[RESOLVED]` prefix in the "Current (wrong)" column. Remove resolved items from
Tier 4 / Clarification sections.

